FBIS4-34152 "drlat116_c_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 MEXICO Deputies Sign Declaration Supporting Cuba Deputies Sign Declaration Supporting Cuba PA1506150694 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0430 GMT 15 Jun 94 PA1506150694 Mexico City XEW Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] All parties represented in the Chamber of Deputies signed a political declaration aimed at rejecting the extraterritorial application of any country's law as well as to express their support for any initiative aimed at suppressing the trade blockade against Cuba. Fernando Charleston, a Institutional Revolutionary Party deputy, proceeded to read the declaration endorsing the Chamber of Deputies' support for the Cuban people in their quest for sovereignty and self-determination.
